{"article_id":"4TfubraBVQyaNS1r","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court on Thursday upheld the heart of President Obama ' s health care law ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"ruling","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"the federal government can compel Americans to buy health insurance ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"and striking a new balance for the scope of federal authority in the 21st century .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The ruling lets Mr. Obama continue to push the law ahead of its full implementation in 2014","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"and will likely amp up pressure on a number of states","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"who had been awaiting a court decision","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"before plowing ahead with state requirements .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The complex 5-4 decision is a major legal boost to Mr. Obama","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"just months before he faces voters in a battle for re-election ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"and it complicates matters for Republicans on Capitol Hill ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"who had turned to the courts","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"after their repeated efforts","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to repeal the law","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"fell short in Congress .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"who wrote the controlling opinion ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"attempted a delicate balancing act :","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"the Commerce and Necessary and Proper clauses of the Constitution can not be bent to compel Americans to buy insurance ,","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"but said","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"it is allowed under Congress ' s tax and spending powers ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"which are broader ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"but are subject to the checks of the political system .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"\" The Affordable Care Act ' s requirement","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"that certain individuals pay a financial penalty","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"for not obtaining health insurance","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"may reasonably be characterized as a tax .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Because the Constitution permits such a tax ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"it is not our role to forbid it , or to pass upon its wisdom or fairness , \"","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"he wrote .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"The court ' s four Democratic-appointed justices all joined the Roberts ruling","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"but wrote separately","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"to say","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"they would have allowed the individual mandate under the Commerce Clause , too .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Four justices dissented ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"saying in an opinion","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"written by Justice Antonin Scalia","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"that the court has granted nearly unlimited authority to Congress","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"to control Americans ' lives .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"\" Whatever may be the conceptual limits upon the Commerce Clause and upon the power","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to tax and spend ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"they can not be such","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"as will enable the Federal Government to regulate all private conduct and to compel the states to function as administrators of federal programs , \"","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Justice Scalia wrote .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"They said","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"they would have struck down not only the individual mandate but the rest of the law as well ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"arguing","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"that the other provisions could not have stood","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"without the compulsion","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"of forcing Americans to buy insurance .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Chief Justice Roberts ' ruling also upheld the law ' s massive expansion of Medicaid ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"but said","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"states can not be compelled to expand their own programs through the threat","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"of removing federal funding altogether .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Instead , states have the choice","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"of expanding","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"and collecting new federal money ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"or staying at current coverage and federal funding levels .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"The political fight was already ramping up Thursday morning ,","depth":4},{"id":60,"text":"with Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell saying","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"the court has stripped away the pretense","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"and exposed the tax increases in the law .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"\" The Supreme Court has spoken .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"This law is a tax .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"The bill was sold to the American people on a deception , \"","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Mr. McConnell said ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"adding","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"that the GOP will continue to pushing","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"to ax the law .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"\" The court ' s ruling doesn ' t mark the end of the debate .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"It marks a fresh start on the road","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to repeal , \"","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"And Majority leader Eric Cantor said","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"the House will vote to repeal the health care law next month ,","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"delivering on GOP promises","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"to try to repeal the rest of the law","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"even if the court upheld it .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"\" The Court ' s decision brings into focus the choice","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"the American people have about the direction of our country , \"","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"\" The president and his party believe in massive government intrusions","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that increase costs","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"and take decisions away from patients . \"","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"But Democrats said","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"the ruling will give them time","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"to implement the law","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"and sell its benefits to the public ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"even as they plan tweaks .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"\" No one thinks","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"this law is perfect , \"","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"said Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid , Nevada Democrat .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"\" But Democrats have proven","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"we ' re willing to work with Republicans","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"to improve the problems","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that exist in this law or any other law . \"","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"All eyes have been on the court","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"ever since the justices announced","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"they would hear major constitutional challenges against the Affordable Care Act .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"The individual mandate","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"to buy insurance","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"or pay a fine","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"was at the heart of the struggle ,","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"marking the first time","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"the federal government had tried to require all Americans to buy a particular good or service .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"While opponents said","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"it violated individual freedom ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"the administration said","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"since everyone consumes health care at some point ,","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"government can control when they begin to pay for it .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"The justices held a marathon three-day series of oral arguments in March","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"and then retreated behind closed doors","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"to deliberate","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"and write their opinions .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"The conflict gave the Supreme Court a chance","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"to try to spell out the federal government ' s relationship with states and individuals more clearly than ever before ,","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"indicating where the government ' s powers","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"to tax ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"to regulate interstate commerce","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"and to enact \" necessary and proper \" laws","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"began and ended .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"Voters have been sharply polarized over the law since the beginning ,","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"and the court ' s ruling is likely to dominate the presidential campaign","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"as Mr. Obama tries to fend off presumptive Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"who himself signed a pioneering health law as governor of Massachusetts .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"The Supreme Court ' s decision comes after more than two years of courtroom battles over the 2010 law .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"As soon as Mr. Obama signed the law ,","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"Virginia Attorney General Ken Cuccinelli filed a lawsuit","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"challenging the individual mandate ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"and in the ensuing year more than half of the states united","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"to challenge the mandate and the bill ' s massive expansion of Medicaid ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"which is the federal-state health program for the poor .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"The court challenges have left the law in limbo for many .","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"Some states started working","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"on setting up their mandatory insurance exchanges .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"But other states ,","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"especially those","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"run by Republicans ,","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"decided to sit back","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"and wait for the ruling","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"before they made any moves .","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"Throughout , the Obama administration touted the immediate benefits of the law :","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"more federal support for prescription drugs for some Medicare beneficiaries ; children up to 26 years of age","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"who are able to stay on their parents ' health policies ; and an end to limits on coverage , such as preexisting conditions .","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"But the health care deliberations also helped spawn the tea party political movement","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"that powered Republicans to victories in the 2010 elections","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"and gave them control of the House","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"which has since voted dozens of times to repeal all or part of the law .","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"Those efforts have almost always fallen short ,","depth":7},{"id":151,"text":"but the administration has accepted some changes .","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"Mr. Obama has signed bills","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"that repealed an onerous business reporting requirement","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"and two other bills","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"that have cut the levels of health exchange subsidy overpayments","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"that would have been allowed .","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"In those last two cases the changes were made","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"so the money could be used for other government priorities .","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"And the administration on its own said","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"it will not move forward with the CLASS Act , a part of the bill","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"championed by the late Sen. Edward M. Kennedy","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"that was designed","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"to cover long-term care ,","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"but which all sides now agree","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"is fiscally unsustainable as written .","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"Throughout , both sides knew","depth":6},{"id":167,"text":"a final ruling from the court would be decisive .","depth":6},{"id":168,"text":"Major insurers such as United Healthcare and Aetna had already announced","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"they would keep some of the law ' s most popular provisions","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"even if it was overturned ,","depth":8},{"id":171,"text":"including the mandate","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"to include children up to age 26 on their parents ' policies","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"and fully cover some preventative services","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"without charging a co-pay .","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"The Supreme Court had its pick from a number of cases","depth":5},{"id":176,"text":"that wound their way through the justice system ,","depth":5},{"id":177,"text":"but chose to hear one","depth":5},{"id":178,"text":"decided by the 11th Circuit","depth":7},{"id":179,"text":"- the only appeals court","depth":7},{"id":180,"text":"to throw out the individual mandate","depth":7},{"id":181,"text":"but uphold the rest of the law .","depth":7},{"id":182,"text":"During oral arguments the justices grappled with a number of major constitutional issues ,","depth":7},{"id":183,"text":"including whether requiring Americans to buy health care violates their liberty ,","depth":8},{"id":184,"text":"how much of the law could function","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"without the individual mandate","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"and whether states can opt out of the Medicaid expansion","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"without losing out on new federal dollars .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"The question about the individual mandate garnered the most public attention ,","depth":7},{"id":189,"text":"widely seen as a referendum on how much influence the federal government may assert over Americans ' purchasing decisions .","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"Many court-watchers said post-ruling","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"that the court appeared more likely to strike down the mandate","depth":9},{"id":192,"text":"after Justice Anthony M. Kennedy and Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr.","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"- expected to be swing votes -","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"were especially tough on Solicitor General Donald Verrilli ,","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"who argued for the administration .","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"The justices seemed to agree","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"that striking down the mandate would dramatically alter the rest of the law ,","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"but disagreed on which route to take .","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"The Republican-appointed justices appeared to lean toward scrapping the whole thing","depth":9},{"id":200,"text":"while the Democrat-appointed justices said","depth":10},{"id":201,"text":"that ' s a decision for Congress to make .","depth":10},{"id":202,"text":"Each sides faced the challenge","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"of describing limits to the power","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"they sought .","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"When the justices challenged him to name something","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"the government couldn ' t do","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"if it could require Americans to buy health coverage ,","depth":9},{"id":208,"text":"Mr. Verrilli said","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"that health insurance is unique","depth":10},{"id":210,"text":"because","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"if anyone can ' t pay for their own health care ,","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"those costs are shifted onto other people .","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"Meanwhile , attorney Paul Clement ,","depth":7},{"id":214,"text":"who argued for the National Federation of Independent Businesses and 26 states","depth":8},{"id":215,"text":"opposing the law ,","depth":8},{"id":216,"text":"struggled to explain","depth":6},{"id":217,"text":"why the states couldn ' t reject all sort of rules","depth":7},{"id":218,"text":"attached to federal programs","depth":7},{"id":219,"text":"if they could reject the Medicaid expansion .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":439,"left":316,"right":438,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":316,"left":278,"right":315,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":234,"right":277,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":227,"right":233,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":223,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":222,"right":3,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":0,"right":221,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":226,"left":4,"right":225,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":225,"left":5,"right":224,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":228,"right":232,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":10,"right":231,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":11,"right":230,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":229,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":229,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":249,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":249,"left":236,"right":248,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":236,"left":235,"right":17,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":235,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":237,"right":247,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":237,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":247,"left":240,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":20,"right":239,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":239,"left":21,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":246,"left":245,"right":30,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":243,"right":244,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":242,"right":27,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":24,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":28,"right":29,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":276,"left":268,"right":275,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":268,"left":252,"right":267,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":250,"right":251,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":31,"right":32,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":251,"left":33,"right":34,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":267,"left":261,"right":266,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":256,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":35,"right":255,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":253,"right":254,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":253,"left":36,"right":37,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":259,"right":44,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":257,"right":258,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":257,"left":40,"right":